Road accident involving seven vehicles at Migaa, near Salgaa along the Nakuru-Eldoret highwayOne person died on the spot while several others sustained serious injuries in a road accident at Migaa near Salgaa on the Nakuru-Eldoret highway. The accident involved seven vehicles, among them two personal cars, a bus, a truck and three trailers. Rongai police boss Joseph Kioko said the crash occurred at around 9.30pm on Sunday. Mr Kioko said one of the drivers of trailers that was carrying maize from Eldoret town lost control of the vehicle, resulting in the accident. Kennedy Kamau, an eyewitness, said the driver of the trailer failed to stop the vehicle. [Mercy Kahenda]&nbsp;